Three phased improvements to make the pipeline aware of video genre
and extend Stage 01 / 04 for code-bearing playlists.

## Stage 00.5: Router (new)

- `pipeline_youtube/genres.py` with `Genre` enum + `CODE_BEARING_GENRES`
  frozenset gate + `classify_playlist_genre()` (single haiku call, ~$0.01
  per playlist).
- Wired into `main.py` after `fetch_metadata`; result logged as
  `genre: coding (code_bearing=True) — <rationale>`.
- Errors (network, parse, unknown enum) collapse to `Genre.OTHER` so
  downstream features default to current behavior.
- Added `router` to `_MODEL_KEYS`; defaults to haiku regardless of
  `--model`.

## Stage 01 extension: GitHub code fetch (gated)

- `pipeline_youtube/code_fetch.py`:
  - `fetch_video_description()` via per-video yt-dlp extract.
  - Regex-based GitHub blob / Gist / repo URL extraction.
  - Raw content fetch (urllib, built-in) with 5-URL / 50 KB caps.
  - `render_code_section()` appends `## 関連コード` with fenced code
    blocks (language detected from extension).
- `run_stage_scripts()` gains `include_code_blocks: bool = False`
  parameter, threaded through `_process_video` / `_run_videos_concurrent`
  from the `code_bearing` flag.
- Repo-level URLs intentionally skipped (README noise > signal).

## Stage 04 extension: concept/practice split (gated)

- `LEARNING_CODE_BEARING_ADDENDUM` appended to system prompt when
  `code_bearing=True`. Instructs the model to emit two top-level
  `# 概念 (Concepts)` / `# 実践 (Practice)` sections and splits the
  existing `<種別>` categories between them.
- Addendum references `## 関連コード` so the Leader can cite fetched
  GitHub snippets in the practice section.

## Tests

- `test_genres.py` (17), `test_code_fetch.py` (27),
  `test_learning_code_bearing.py` (3).
- Updated `test_config_models.py` for the new `router` model key.
- Updated `test_e2e_playlist.py` to stub `classify_playlist_genre` and
  accept the new `include_code_blocks` kwarg.
- Total: 506 → 553 passed.

## README

Added a new "ジャンル判定 (Router) とジャンル別分岐" section documenting
the gate, GitHub URL constraints, and error-fallback behavior. Updated
stage list and test count.

